			    STPJS 374</div>
  <p class="cont">ciples are poured out all over the Scriptures. When things that are of the greatest importance are
  passed over by the weak-minded men without even a thought, I want to see truth in all its
  bearings and hug it to my bosom. I believe all that God ever revealed,<span class="footRef">1</span> and I never hear of a man
  being damned for believing too much; but they are damned for unbelief.<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <p class="std">They found fault with Jesus Christ because He said He was the Son of God, and made
  Himself equal with God.<span class="footRef">3</span> They say of me, like they did of the Apostles of old, that I must be put
  down.<span class="footRef">4</span> What did Jesus say? &ldquo;Is it not written in your law, I said, Ye are Gods?<span class="footRef">5</span> If He called them
  Gods unto whom the word of God came, and the Scriptures cannot be broken, say ye of Him
  whom the Father hath sanctified and sent into the world, Thou blasphemest; because I said I am
  the Son of God?&rdquo;<span class="footRef">6</span> It was through Him that they drank of the spiritual rock.<span class="footRef">7</span> Of course He would
  take the honor to Himself.<span class="footRef">8</span> Jesus, if they were called Gods unto whom the word of God came,
  why should it be thought blasphemy that I should say I am the Son of God?<span class="footRef">9</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Eternal Glories</div>
  <p class="std">Go and read the vision in the Book of Covenants.<span class="footRef">10</span> There is clearly illustrated glory upon
  glory&mdash;one glory of the sun, another glory of the moon, and a glory of the stars;<span class="footRef">11</span> and as one star
  differeth from another star in glory,<span class="footRef">12</span> even so do they of the telestial world differ in glory,<span class="footRef">13</span> and
  every man who reigns in celestial glory is a God to his dominions.<span class="footRef">14</span> By the apostates admitting the
  testimony of the Doctrine and Covenants they damn themselves. Paul, what do you say? They
  impeached Paul<span class="footRef">15</span> and all went and left him. Paul had seven churches,<span class="footRef">16</span> and they drove him off from
  among them;<span class="footRef">17</span> and yet they cannot do it by me. I rejoice in that. My testimony is good.</p>
  <p class="std">Paul says, &ldquo;There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of
  the stars; for one star differeth from another star in glory. So also is the resurrection of the dead.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">18</span>
  They who obtain a glorious resurrection<span class="footRef">19</span> from the dead, are exalted far above principalities, powers,
  thrones, dominions and angels,<span class="footRef">20</span> and are expressly declared to be heirs of God and joint heirs with
  Jesus Christ,<span class="footRef">21</span> all having eternal power.<span class="footRef">22</span></p>
  <p class="std">These Scriptures are a mixture of very strange doctrines</p>
